<div style="font-family:system-ui,-apple-system,sans-serif; color:#333; max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">

<div style="font-size:18px; font-weight:800; color:#1a1a1a; margin:24px 0 12px 0; padding-bottom:6px; border-bottom:2px solid #999;">
  📰 GENERAL INTEREST / SCIENCE
</div>

<div style="background:#f8f8f8; border:1px solid #e0e0e0; border-radius:10px; padding:16px 18px; margin-bottom:12px;">
  <div style="font-size:15px; font-weight:700; margin-bottom:6px;">
    <a href="https://www.reuters.com/science/cretaceous-kraken-prowled-seas-during-age-dinosaurs-2026-04-23/" style="color:#1a1a1a; text-decoration:none;">Ancient Kraken-like Octopus Discovered</a>
  </div>
  <div style="font-size:13px; color:#555; margin-bottom:10px; line-height:1.5;">
    Scientists confirmed Nanaimoteuthis haggarti, a finned octopus from 86–72 million years ago, grew up to 61 feet long — bigger than a school bus. The discovery rewrites understanding of ancient ocean food webs and suggests these creatures were apex predators in Cretaceous seas.
  </div>
  <div style="margin-bottom:8px;">
    <span style="font-size:11px; background:#e8e8e8; color:#666; padding:2px 8px; border-radius:4px;">Reuters</span>
    <span style="font-size:11px; background:#999; color:#fff; padding:2px 8px; border-radius:4px; font-weight:600; margin-left:6px;">GENERAL INTEREST</span>
  </div>
  <div style="font-size:12px; color:#4f9cf9; background:#eef5ff; padding:8px 12px; border-radius:6px; margin-top:8px;">
    👉 <strong>Why this matters:</strong> A fascinating reminder that the natural world still holds massive surprises — and that Norse legends of giant sea creatures may have been based on real animals.
  </div>
</div>

